LEGIONELLOSIS - USA (07): (HAWAII) FATAL, NOSOCOMIAL
****************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Wed 20 Jun 2018
Source: KITV [edited]
http://www.kitv.com/story/38463629/legionella-outbreak-investigated-by-hawaii-health-department


The State Health Department is investigating 4 cases of _Legionella_ infection, a [type of pneumonia], all treated at Queen's Medical Center.

It [_Legionella_] went airborne from [contaminated] water through spraying, misting, and splashing.

The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention [CDC] is also on board, trying to find out whether exposure came from inside [nosocomial] or outside the hospital [community-acquired].

People with weak immune systems are more vulnerable to _Legionella_ infection, but it is not necessarily transmitted person-to-person.

The recommendation is for high-risk patients to avoid exposure to tap water at Queen's.

[Byline: Shannon Manamtam]

